external_knowledge:
- 30 days is considered a month in this context for simplicity; 
- 'average views per article' refers to the total number of views divided by the number of articles; 
- 'more than 5 published articles' applies to the last 30 days.

sql:
SELECT SUM(views) AS total_views
FROM views
WHERE article_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(engagement_id) AS total_engagement
FROM user_engagements
WHERE article_id = 1;

SELECT article_id, MAX(timestamp) AS latest_view
FROM views
GROUP BY article_id;
